---
import BaseLayout from '../components/layout/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Work with me"
  description="Narrative strategy and editorial systems for organisations that have strong research and insight but aren't extracting full value from it."
>
  <article class="container-site py-20">
    <div class="max-w-2xl">

      <header class="mb-16">
        <p class="t-label mb-6">Work with me</p>
        <h1 class="t-display mb-6">You have the research.<br />I'll find the argument.</h1>
        <p class="t-body text-lg leading-relaxed">
          Narrative strategy for organisations sitting on strong insight that is not working as hard as it should.
        </p>
      </header>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <section class="mb-16">
        <div class="prose-section">
          <p>Most organisations already have more insight than they realise: research reports, customer stories, event takeaways, advisory board discussions, sales feedback and market analysis.</p>
          <p>The problem is not the absence of evidence. The problem is that the evidence is scattered.</p>
          <p>A report gets published. A few articles are written. A customer story becomes a proof point. An event produces useful conversations. Then the next campaign starts, and the learning disappears into another folder, deck or Teams thread.</p>
          <p>Editorial Intelligence solves that problem by building the narrative layer: the argument, structure and reusable system that connects the evidence, gives it direction and helps it compound over time.</p>
          <p>That is the gap I work in.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="t-label mb-8">Who this is for</h2>
        <div class="prose-section">
          <p>B2B organisations, typically in fintech, SaaS, professional services or complex markets, where:</p>
          <ul class="work-list">
            <li>You have commissioned research that underperformed relative to the investment</li>
            <li>You have customer insight that has not been turned into a coherent strategic narrative</li>
            <li>Your content programme resets with every campaign instead of building momentum</li>
            <li>Your events generate useful signals, but those signals are not reused strategically</li>
            <li>Your teams produce strong individual assets, but the wider argument is unclear</li>
            <li>You are about to invest in more content but suspect that more content is not the real answer</li>
          </ul>
          <p>The right engagement starts with a clear-eyed look at what you already have.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="t-label mb-8">How it works</h2>

        <div class="engagement-block">
          <div class="engagement-header">
            <span class="engagement-number">01</span>
            <h3 class="engagement-title">Narrative audit</h3>
          </div>
          <div class="prose-section">
            <p>A structured review of your existing research, content, customer insight and market evidence. I read what you have, identify what the evidence is actually saying, and assess what narrative case it supports — as well as what is being missed.</p>
            <p>You get a clear written assessment covering:</p>
            <ul class="work-list">
              <li>Your strongest through-lines</li>
              <li>The evidence with the most strategic value</li>
              <li>Where the current narrative is fragmented</li>
              <li>What your existing assets could become</li>
              <li>What a connected narrative system would look like</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="engagement-outcome">Outcome: a narrative audit report. Fixed scope, fixed fee. Typically two to three weeks.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="engagement-block">
          <div class="engagement-header">
            <span class="engagement-number">02</span>
            <h3 class="engagement-title">Narrative development</h3>
          </div>
          <div class="prose-section">
            <p>From the audit, the next stage is building the narrative itself. That might mean developing the strategic argument, creating a framework, structuring a thought leadership platform, or designing a content system that connects your existing and future assets.</p>
            <p>The aim is not to create another campaign message. It is to create a narrative structure that can be reused across content, comms, sales, events and future research.</p>
            <p>Possible outputs include:</p>
            <ul class="work-list">
              <li>Strategic narrative brief</li>
              <li>Thought leadership platform</li>
              <li>Editorial framework</li>
              <li>Content activation model</li>
              <li>Research-to-content system</li>
              <li>Messaging architecture</li>
              <li>Evidence library structure</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="engagement-outcome">Outcome: defined with you based on what the audit surfaces.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="engagement-block">
          <div class="engagement-header">
            <span class="engagement-number">03</span>
            <h3 class="engagement-title">Ongoing advisory</h3>
          </div>
          <div class="prose-section">
            <p>For teams that want a strategic editorial perspective over time. This can include reviewing how new research connects to existing narratives, sense-checking content decisions against the strategic argument, identifying new signals, and advising when the narrative needs to evolve.</p>
            <p class="engagement-outcome">Outcome: retainer-based. Scope defined per engagement.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="t-label mb-8">What I bring</h2>
        <div class="prose-section">
          <p>More than a decade of editorial and content experience in complex B2B markets — developing research-led narratives, turning customer insight into useful evidence, and connecting organisational knowledge into systems that outlast individual campaigns.</p>
          <p>The work on this site documents that practice.</p>
          <p><a href="/narratives/hidden-hours" class="text-[var(--color-accent)] no-underline hover:underline">Hidden Hours</a> shows how research can become more than a report: a narrative platform, content series, diagnostic idea and source of ongoing market intelligence.</p>
          <p><a href="/narratives/winning-in-small" class="text-[var(--color-accent)] no-underline hover:underline">Winning in Small</a> shows how event insight, customer stories and survey data can be synthesised into a clearer strategic argument.</p>
          <p>The <a href="/applications" class="text-[var(--color-accent)] no-underline hover:underline">Applications</a> section shows how Editorial Intelligence can be used across research, events, customer stories, AI workflows and content activation.</p>
          <p>I am not an agency. I work on a small number of engagements at a time, which means the thinking is mine rather than delegated.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="t-label mb-8">Start a conversation</h2>
        <div class="prose-section">
          <p>Most first conversations are straightforward: you want to understand the methodology, I want to understand the problem. If there is a useful fit, we go from there.</p>
          <p>If what is on this site resonates with what you are working on, that is enough reason to get in touch.</p>
          <a href="mailto:asavin@contentconsultant.net" class="contact-cta">
            asavin@contentconsultant.net
            <span class="contact-cta-arrow">→</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>

    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .prose-section {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .prose-section p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
  }

  .work-list {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .work-list li {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .work-list li::before {
    content: '→';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .engagement-block {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    padding-bottom: 2.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-rule, #2c2920);
  }

  .engagement-block:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
    padding-bottom: 0;
  }

  .engagement-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .engagement-number {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    opacity: 0.7;
  }

  .engagement-title {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .contact-cta {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 35%, transparent);
    padding-bottom: 2px;
    transition: border-color 0.2s;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
  }

  .contact-cta:hover {
    border-color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .contact-cta-arrow {
    transition: transform 0.2s;
  }

  .contact-cta:hover .contact-cta-arrow {
    transform: translateX(3px);
  }

  .engagement-outcome {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem !important;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary) !important;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
  }
</style>
